Patch Set 1:

> Looks like this job is still using OSC instead of glance
 > image-create-via-import command

No, it's using import:

 openstack --os-cloud=devstack-admin --os-region-name=RegionOne image create cirros-0.5.1-x86_64-disk --public --container-format bare --disk-format qcow2 --import

In OSC, 'image create --import' does the import workflow. I think you can tell that this is the case because the image is in queued state, right?

 | status           | queued  

I just pushed up more of this which adds a post-run task that makes sure the image got the properties I added. You can see in the glance log that tasks are running and it seemed to do the metadata injection:
